metadata.name: sakura
metadata.description:
The Japanese cherry blossom, or sakura, is Japanâ€™s national flower, and it represents hope and renewal. Since cherry trees only bloom for a short period in the spring, the beauty of the flowers also symbolizes the fleeting nature of life.

"How many, many things  
They call to mind  
These cherry-blossoms!"

Matsuo Basho
